odeling {#structural-vs-functional-trajectory-modeling .unnumbered}

We decomposed TLS maturation into two axes:

1. Structural pseudotime -- based on combined GC + T--B + Stromal
 > genes; represents tissue organization and cellular composition.

2. Functional pseudotime -- based on GC genes, representing B-cell
 > proliferation and differentiation, TFH, proliferation and other GC
 > functions.

Each axis was reconstructed using SCORPIUS pseudotime inference and
visualized by UMAP.

A strong positive correlation between structural and functional
pseudotime indicated synchronized spatial and functional TLS maturation.

